substep.action:
From the Stage-1 dossier + resolved rules, derive 1–3 candidate architectures. For EACH option decide, BY DDD ROLE using the resolved TOPOLOGY tokens:
      • which resolved LAYER(S) own the change (using the resolved LAYER NAMES, never literals);
      • new aggregate vs extend an existing aggregate;
      • the command (write / handler role) vs query (read / service role) split;
      • the cross-context contract shape (the shared-kernel contract role), when contexts interact;
      • domain events emitted (the domain-event / EventRecord role), if any;
      • the persistence seam (the infrastructure / framework-adapter role under the resolved namespace).

Build the decision record from `templates/_base/adr.md`, filling its placeholders:
      • `{{adr_number}}` — the next number by scanning existing `docs/architecture/adr-*.md` (greenfield → start at 1);
      • `{{decision_title}}` — the feature + chosen architecture, by DDD role;
      • `{{status}}` — Accepted (the option is now approved, or auto-selected under auto_approve);
      • `{{date}}` — today's date;
      • `{{bc_name}}` — the resolved bounded-context / module name from the TOPOLOGY tokens;
      • Context / Decision Drivers / Decision — the dossier facts and resolved rules that drove the choice;
      • Consequences (Positive / Negative / Neutral) — the chosen option's trade-offs;
      • Alternatives Considered — the rejected options with their reason-rejected (or "none viable" for the single-option case).
